Hochman-H-I.  Feins-N-R.  Rubin-R.  Gould-J.

Chloride losing diarrhoea and metabolic alkalosis in an infant with
cystic fibrosis.

ALKALOSIS: et.  CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: co.  DIARRHEA-INFANTILE: et.

CASE-REPORT.  CHLORIDES: me.  FECES: an.  FEMALE.  HUMAN.
ILEOSTOMY:  ae.  INFANT-NEWBORN.

A case of hypochloraemic metabolic alkalosis in an infant with
chloride losing ileostomy drainage and cystic fibrosis is described.
It is speculated that intestinal loss of chloride played a major role
in the development of metabolic alkalosis.

